---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Thibaut LEFRANCOIS" altLocaleUrl="/">
  <h2 class="pb-6 text-xl font-semibold italic md:text-2xl">
    full-stack &amp; creative developer
  </h2>
  <div
    class="text-sage-11 flex max-w-prose flex-col gap-5 text-base leading-relaxed md:gap-6"
  >
    <p>
      This portfolio was published far too early, intentionally. I wanted
      somewhere to write, and Astro was the tool I'd chosen for both the blog
      and the portfolio, so I shipped what I had.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <a href="/en/blog" class="text-sage-12 underline">blog</a> is where I document
      what I learn every day: small experiments, discoveries, and web explorations
      that feed my
      <a href="/en/projects" class="text-sage-12 underline">project list</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Eventually, these projects will be presented here in a more creative way.
      For now, I'm still practising to get there.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l69ztiHjXb1Q0WuAgiSPmeoh-eoq8Ep9/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-sage-12 underline"
        >View my CV &rarr;<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a
      >
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
